{"parse":{"title":"The Ides of April","pageid":36746030,"revid":859876212,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">The Ides of April <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Ides+of+April&amp;rft.author=%5B%5BLindsey+Davis%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=11+April+2013&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BHodder+%26+Stoughton%5D%5D&amp;rft.pages=356&amp;rft.series=%5B%5BFlavia+Albia%7CFlavia+Albia+%28Falco%3A+The+New+Generation%29%5D%5D\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Ides_of_April_cover.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Ides of April cover.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/0d/Ides_of_April_cover.jpg/220px-Ides_of_April_cover.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"336\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/0/0d/Ides_of_April_cover.jpg 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"255\" data-file-height=\"390\" /></a><div>Front cover of UK hardback</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Lindsey_Davis\" title=\"Lindsey Davis\">Lindsey Davis</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\nUK</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Series</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Flavia_Albia\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Flavia Albia\">Flavia Albia (Falco: The New Generation)</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Genre</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Historical_mystery\" title=\"Historical mystery\">historical mystery</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Crime_novel\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Crime novel\">crime novel</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Hodder_%26_Stoughton\" title=\"Hodder &amp; Stoughton\">Hodder &amp; Stoughton</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Publication date</div></th><td>\n11 April 2013</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Pages</th><td>\n356</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-4447-5581-7\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-1-4447-5581-7\">978-1-4447-5581-7</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Followed&#160;by</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/wiki/Enemies_at_Home\" title=\"Enemies at Home\">Enemies at Home</a></i></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>The Ides of April</b></i> is a 2013 <a href=\"/wiki/Historical_mystery\" title=\"Historical mystery\">historical mystery</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Crime_novel\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Crime novel\">crime novel</a> by <a href=\"/wiki/Lindsey_Davis\" title=\"Lindsey Davis\">Lindsey Davis</a> and the first book in the <a href=\"/wiki/Flavia_Albia\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Flavia Albia\">Flavia Albia Mysteries</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> (Falco: The New Generation)<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>) series.  Set in March and April AD 89, in the <a href=\"/wiki/Aventine_Hill\" title=\"Aventine Hill\">Aventine Hill</a> area of <a href=\"/wiki/Ancient_Rome\" title=\"Ancient Rome\">Ancient Rome</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> the novel stars <a href=\"/wiki/Flavia_Albia\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Flavia Albia\">Flavia Albia</a>, the British-born adopted daughter of <a href=\"/wiki/Marcus_Didius_Falco\" title=\"Marcus Didius Falco\">Marcus Didius Falco</a> (the hero of the author's 20-volume Marcus Didius Falco Mysteries series, published from 1989 to 2010).  Albia, a widow, works as a \"<a href=\"/wiki/Delator\" title=\"Delator\">delatrix</a>\" (detective or private informer) in ancient Rome, like Falco.  The book's front cover image depicts a small glass pot and a needle dipped in blood. It carries the strapline, \"Falco: The New Generation\".\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Connections_to_the_Falco_series\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Connections to the Falco series</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Reception\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Reception</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Further_reading\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Further reading</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Connections_to_the_Falco_series\">Connections to the Falco series</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Ides_of_April&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Connections to the Falco series\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Falco and his partner Helena are included in the \"Cast list\" in the book, and Flavia Albia describes them and their household and visits them during the course of the story, but they do not appear directly in the text. Helena's two brothers are mentioned as being lawyers. Falco's old friend Petro is not mentioned in the cast list, but is referred to as Flavia Albia's \"uncle\" in the text.\n</p><p>Falco's young brother Postumus, the result of Thalia's pregnancy in <i><a href=\"/wiki/Nemesis_(Lindsey_Davis_novel)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Nemesis (Lindsey Davis novel)\">Nemesis</a></i>, is now an awkward 11-year-old, who appears in the book.\n</p><p>Flavia Albia uses Falco's old apartment in Fountain Court as her office, and lives elsewhere in the same building. In <i><a href=\"/wiki/Enemies_at_Home\" title=\"Enemies at Home\">Enemies at Home</a></i>, it is revealed that the Didii bought over the Fountain Court block, possibly from <a href=\"/wiki/Marcus_Didius_Falco#Acquaintances\" title=\"Marcus Didius Falco\">Smaractus</a>, Falco's former landlord.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Reception\">Reception</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Ides_of_April&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Reception\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2><p>\nThe <i><a href=\"/wiki/Irish_Times\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Irish Times\">Irish Times</a></i> reviewer wrote: \"Irreverent, resourceful and hard-boiled in her patter, Flavia is a heroine to rival her contemporary counterparts VI Warshawski and Kinsey Milhone.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>  <a href=\"/wiki/Tom_Holland_(author)\" title=\"Tom Holland (author)\">Tom Holland</a> reviewed the book for <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Guardian\" title=\"The Guardian\">The Guardian</a></i><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> and ended:</p><style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r856303468\">.mw-parser-output .templatequote{overflow:hidden;margin:1em 0;padding:0 40px}.mw-parser-output .templatequote .templatequotecite{line-height:1.5em;text-align:left;padding-left:1.6em;margin-top:0}</style><blockquote class=\"templatequote\"><p>\"If you want to see the worst manners, filthiest motives and saddest ethics,\" [Albia] says of her own line of work, \"this is the profession.\" Thankfully, though \u2013 and as ever with a Davis novel \u2013 the narration of these horrors is done so delightfully that the final impression is curiously warm and uplifting.</p><div class=\"templatequotecite\">\u2014&#8201;<cite>Tom Holland, <i>The Guardian</i></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Ides_of_April&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Davis, Lindsey (June 11, 2013). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.amazon.com/April-Flavia-Albia-Mysteries-Mystery/dp/1482100797\"><i>The Ides of April </i>(Flavia Albia Mysteries) (Flavia Albia Mystery)<i><span></span></i></a> (Unabridged ed.). AudioGO. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1482100792\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-1482100792\">978-1482100792</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Ides+of+April+%28Flavia+Albia+Mysteries%29+%28Flavia+Albia+Mystery%29&amp;rft.edition=Unabridged&amp;rft.pub=AudioGO&amp;rft.date=2013-06-11&amp;rft.isbn=978-1482100792&amp;rft.au=Davis%2C+Lindsey&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FApril-Flavia-Albia-Mysteries-Mystery%2Fdp%2F1482100797&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Ides+of+April\" class=\"Z3988\"><spa